  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACT Appeal SYR121 / DEC / IOCC Syria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The scale of the crisis and violence in Syria has escalated and thus a considerable increase in humanitarian assistance and donor contributions is required to address the growing humanitarian needs. The urgency of the situation and the scale of needs cannot be overstated. Working through IOCC and their local partner inside Syria provides access to hard to reach families. The needs inside the country are extensive, with massive damage to infrastructure, violence and loss of assets at household level. This is a 6 month project to meet immediate and basic requirements for families to improve their health and security.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">These DEC funds are being utilised to support a proportion of IOCC&apos;s work as part of the ACT Appeal, earmarked for families inside Syria affected by the ongoing violent conflict and displacement. The work to be supported using these funds is for 600 food kits, NFIs for 500 families, CFW for 60 people, and rental assistance for 250 families.</narrative>
  </description>
